<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,150,176]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Remarks</emphasis>
. The specimens recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[662,871,150,176]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Zhejiang Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[882,952,150,176]" name="China" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">China</collectingCountry>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[994,1109,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[994,1109,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Xiao, G. - R." box="[1151,1436,150,176]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="285 - 296" refId="ref79270" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Xiao, G. - R. (2006) Some leaf-rolling sawflies (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae, Pamphiliinae) from China in the collection of the Research Institute of Forest Protection, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing. In: Blank, S. M., Schmidt, S. &amp; Taeger, A. (Eds), Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, pp. 285 - 296." type="book chapter" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Xiao (2006)</bibRefCitation>
belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara &amp; Wei, 2016" authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2016" box="[263,613,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atra">
<emphasis box="[263,344,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. atra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C." box="[350,613,186,212]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="301 - 318" refId="ref79214" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C. (2016) Leaf-rolling sawflies (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae, Pamphiliinae) of Tianmushan Mountains, Zhejiang Province, China. Zootaxa, 4072 (3), 301 - 318. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4072.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Shinohara &amp; Wei, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C." box="[627,890,186,212]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="301 - 318" refId="ref79214" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C. (2016) Leaf-rolling sawflies (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae, Pamphiliinae) of Tianmushan Mountains, Zhejiang Province, China. Zootaxa, 4072 (3), 301 - 318. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4072.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Shinohara &amp; Wei 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[938,1008,186,212]" name="China" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[1019,1134,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[1019,1134,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found only in the northeastern part (
<collectingRegion box="[355,409,222,248]" country="China" name="Jilin" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Jilin</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
Morphologically, this species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[749,934,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis box="[749,934,258,285]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
particularly in having a comparatively long flagellomere 1 and a similar structure of the male clypeus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[832,1044,294,320]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed these two species in his 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[491,647,330,357]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteicornis">
<emphasis box="[491,647,330,357]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. luteicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName box="[844,1001,330,357]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteicornis">
<emphasis box="[844,1001,330,357]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. luteicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This placement was supported by our NaK analysis, where the nearest neighbour of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[766,883,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[766,883,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of only 0.2%, was 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[361,475,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[361,475,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[528,711,402,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis box="[528,711,402,429]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a clade with 100% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1309,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="240.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,186,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@240.[172,1415,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="240" captionText="FIGURE 153. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Onycholyda." pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
). However, in the COI analysis, the nearest neighbour, diverging by a minimum of 2.6%, was 
<emphasis box="[1086,1266,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1262,438,465]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viriditibialis">O. viriditibialis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with which 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a clade with 100% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[742,841,474,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 138" captionStartId="227.[151,250,1515,1539]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,187,1487]" captionTargetId="figure-19@227.[151,1436,181,1491]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="FIGURE 138. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Onycholyda, part 1." pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 138</figureCitation>
). The maximum 
<emphasis box="[1033,1047,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">p</emphasis>
-distance between 
<specimenCount box="[1256,1437,474,500]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[182,297,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[182,297,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[365,540,510,536]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
was 0.6% in COI and 0% in NaK.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
It is interesting that the known distributions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" box="[745,863,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[745,863,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[922,1108,546,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis box="[922,1108,546,573]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not overlap. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Onycholyda armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a continental species and 
<taxonomicName box="[551,734,582,609]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kumamotonis">
<emphasis box="[551,734,582,609]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. kumamotonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs only in 
<collectingCountry box="[907,971,583,609]" name="Japan" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Japan</collectingCountry>
and Sakhalin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
